text: Goose Creek is a stream in Caldwell County of Missouri. It is a tributary of Shoal Creek. The headwaters are located at and the confluence with Shoal Creek are at . Goose Creek was so named for the fact it was the hunting ground of geese. ==See also== *List of rivers of Missouri ==References== Category:Rivers of Caldwell County, Missouri Category:Rivers of Missouri
title: Goose Creek (Shoal Creek tributary)
